Definition: rugby) the method of beginning play in which the forwards of each team crouch side by side with locked arms
Example: play starts when the ball is thrown in between them and the two sides compete for possession
Synonyms: scrummage, beginning, rugby, c, the, method, of, play, in, which, forwards, each, team, crouch, side, by, with, locked, arms, starts, when, ball, is, thrown, between, them, and, two, sides, compete, for, possession
Category: noun.act
